events.name: eds-time-picker-time-changed
events.description:
fired when a new time value has been entered/selected and validated. The
detail object has the following format:
```
{
 'dateTime': momentObject,
 'formattedValue': string // displayed time in the time picker. Done by using
                          //`moment.format()` with the time picker current `format`
 'timezone': string       // the timezone of the current
 'info': string           // optionally, shows metadata information such as clockType change
}
```

events.name: eds-time-picker-error
events.description:
fired when there is an error with the time format, such as
   invalid time format
detail object has the following format:
```
{
 'error': string Message about the error
}
```

events.name: eds-time-picker-clear
events.description: fired when the current time is cleared.

properties.name: appendTo
properties.description: appends time picker dropdown menu to any element (e.g. body) by using `appendTo` property of underlying dropdown component.

properties.name: clockType
properties.description:
Indicates preference for 12-hour or 24-hour clock format.
 Valid values are 12 or 24.  If 12, the time will display with AM or PM
 period indicator.  Default value is 12.

properties.name: format
properties.description:
The format string used to represent the time value.  Formatting string
values come from [moment.js](http://momentjs.com/docs/#/parsing/string-format/).
Default value is 12 hour format: 'hh:mm A'

properties.name: isError
properties.description: Whether the dropdown is in error state

properties.name: locale
properties.description:
Moment's locale id to change the localization of the date picker.
More information on available [locales](https://github.com/moment/moment/tree/develop/locale)

properties.name: minuteSelectListInterval
properties.description:
For time select list. Specifies interval in minutes for time select
list options. Value must be divisible evenly into 60.  Used to automatically
generate the option values for time select list. Default value is 30.
For example, a value of 10 will render a minutes select list with the
options [12:00, 12:10, 12:20, 12:30, 12:40, 12:50], or a value of 15 will
render a select list with the options [12:00, 12:15, 12:30, 12:45]. To get
hourly time intervals, use 60.
If an invalid value is specified (something not evenly divided into 60,
e.g. 7) an error will be thrown.  Valid values positive whole numbers:
[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 10, 12, 15, 20, 30, 60]

properties.name: momentObj
showTimezoneSelector
properties.description: Indicates whether to show the timezone select list. Default is false

properties.name: tzLabel
properties.description: The label shown above the timezone select list. Default value is 'Timezone'

properties.name: width
properties.description: width property to override the default setting.

EDSTimePicker.description:
The **time picker** is a form element that enables the user to enter a specific
time value (hour, minute, AM/PM) either through text input or by selecting a
time from an interactive time selection widget.
EDSTimePicker.name: Time Picker
EDSTimePicker.usage:
The time picker relies on the [moment.js](https://momentjs.com/docs/) library to process, validate
and format time. By default, the time picker value is not set, but it can be populated by using a moment
object and assigning it to `momentObj`. The moment.js library is available on `window.GEHC.EDS.moment`
to create new moment object.

When a new time has been selected by a user, the `eds-time-picker-time-changed` will be fired.

##### Internationalization
The time picker relies on moment.js for [internationalization](https://momentjs.com/docs/#/i18n/).
You can either create your own locale and load it or use one of the pre-generated ones by just calling
`window.GEHC.EDS.moment.locale(localeString)` with `localeString` being the name of one of
[those files](https://github.com/moment/moment/tree/develop/locale).
